Ferrovial, Pescanova, Sacyr May Move: Spanish Equity Preview

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-04-13T04:00:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/ferrovial-pescanova-sacyr-may-move-spanish-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  Spain ’s IBEX 35 fell 93.8 points, or 0.9 percent, to
10,784.50.  Ferrovial SA (FER)  : Spain’s second-largest builder by
market capitalization signed a 1.31 billion-euro ($1.9 billion)
four-year loan with 32 lenders, the company said in a filing to
regulators. The accord also includes a credit line of 541
million euros. The shares dropped 1.9 percent to 9 euros.  Pescanova SA (PVA)  : The Spanish frozen fish producer
said it will sell 180 million euros of convertible bonds and set
an initial conversion price of 36.24 euros. It will also pay
31.9 million euros to buy back debt with a nominal value of 26.6
million euros, the company said in a regulatory filing. The
shares retreated 1.8 percent to 27.82 euros.  Sacyr Vallehermoso SA (SYV)  : The Spanish builder
completed the sale of 200 million euros of convertible bonds,
the company said in a regulatory filing. The shares declined 0.4
percent to 9.29 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 